ass=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 20, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104sjp1665702803652.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/sjp1665702803652.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/sjp1665702803652.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"sjp1665702803652\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Define Implementation\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Define one or more implementations of a component.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sjp1665702803652__p_d6236e1_d6237e1_d6238e1\">A component cannot have both Uniface and operating system implementations at the same time. However, a component with a Uniface or operating system implementation can also have one or more of the other non-Uniface implementations.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"sjp1665702803652__section_xnh_q3f_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d961905e58\">Buttons</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"sjp1665702803652__ul_qpl_q3f_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sjp1665702803652__li_d3089e1_d3090e1_d3091e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Properties</span> —define the\n               call-out properties of any implementation type other than Uniface or Java. <p class=\"p\" id=\"sjp1665702803652__p_d6242e1_d6243e1_d6244e1\">Call-out is not supported for Java, whereas\n                  call-out from one Uniface component to another requires no property settings. For\n                  implementations that support both call-in and call-out, such as COM , the call-out\n                  mapping is also used as a basis for call-in.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sjp1665702803652__li_d3092e1_d3093e1_d3094e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">New</span>—add implementations to\n               the signature. You cannot add two implementations of the same type. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sjp1665702803652__li_d3095e1_d3096e1_d3097e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Delete</span>—delete an\n               implementation from the signature. <div class=\"note caution note_caution\" id=\"sjp1665702803652__note_vpl_q3f_5cc\"><span class=\"note__title\">CAUTION:</span> If you\n                  delete a Uniface implementation from this list, the corresponding Uniface\n                  component is also deleted from the Uniface repository.</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"sjp1665702803652__section_qbz_q3f_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d961905e88\">Fields</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"sjp1665702803652__ul_ipw_r3f_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sjp1665702803652__li_d3098e1_d3099e1_d3100e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hip1665702803864.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hip1665702803864.html\" title=\"Implementation type defined or available for the component.\">Type</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sjp1665702803652__li_d3101e1_d3102e1_d3103e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dts1665702672586.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dts1665702672586.html\" title=\"Determines the default component implementation used at run time.\">Default Implementation</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sjp1665702803652__li_d3104e1_d3105e1_d3106e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xrw1665702585620.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xrw1665702585620.html\" title=\"Use this property to briefly describe the development object in up to 256 Unicode characters.\">Description</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sjp1665702803652__li_d3107e1_d3108e1_d3109e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bck1665702654827.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bck1665702654827.html\" title=\"Extended description of the global object.\">Comments</a>—for Uniface\n               component implementations, this field is display-only. </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"sjp1665702803652__section_q2g_s3f_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d961905e133\">How to</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"sjp1665702803652__ul_am1_t3f_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sjp1665702803652__li_d3110e1_d3111e1_d3112e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sjp1665702803652__p_d6251e1_d6252e1_d6253e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zzx1665702678830.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zzx1665702678830.html\" title=\"Use the Signature Editor to create or modify component signatures. Signatures of Uniface components are automatically generated during compilation. Signatures of non-Uniface components can be created or imported.\">Define a Component Signature</a>\n</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kqj1665702890051.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Component Implementations</a><p>The component signature specifies the implementation a component, which determines the technology used to deploy it, such as Uniface, C, or Java.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_8422794\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_8422794\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Define Implementation Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 20, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Define Implementation Define one or more implementations of a component. A component cannot have both Uniface and operating system implementations at the same time. However, a component with a Uniface or operating system implementation can also have one or more of the other non-Uniface implementations. Buttons Properties —define the call-out properties of any implementation type other than Uniface or Java. Call-out is not supported for Java, whereas call-out from one Uniface component to another requires no property settings. For implementations that support both call-in and call-out, such as COM , the call-out mapping is also used as a basis for call-in. New —add implementations to the signature. You cannot add two implementations of the same type. Delete —delete an implementation from the signature. CAUTION: If you delete a Uniface implementation from this list, the corresponding Uniface component is also deleted from the Uniface repository. Fields Type Default Implementation Description Comments —for Uniface component implementations, this field is display-only. How to Define a Component Signature Related Links Component Implementations The component signature specifies the implementation a component, which determines the technology used to deploy it, such as Uniface, C, or Java. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}